text: Dabou Department is a department in Lagunes District, Grands-Ponts Region, Ivory Coast. In 2021, 213,582 people lived there. The capital of the department is Dabou. The sub-prefectures of the department are Dabou, Lopou, and Toupah. Dabou Department was created in 1998 as split off from Abidjan Department.
